cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper deals with video object segmentation, which is a problem in computer vision. The use of a Tukey-inspired measure to find foreground objects in low-level vision data suggests that this paper is likely to be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a method that achieves state-of-the-art results, which suggests that it may also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of unsupervised learning and the estimation of reliability of each data source suggest that this paper may also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of multiple segmentation methods and the improvement in the Jaccard measure suggest that this paper may also be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of segmentation in robotics applications suggests that this paper may also be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics).
